Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 450 degrees. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and discard the bottom inch from the @asparagus{6%oz}, then cut into 3-inch pieces. Strip the @thyme{1/4%oz} from the stems, then roughly chop the leaves. Bring the @veggie stock concentrate{1} and @water{3/4%cups} to a low simmer in a #small pot{}.

In a large #baking dish{}, toss together the garlic, asparagus, @grape tomatoes{4%oz}, half the thyme, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and place in the oven for about ~{20%minutes}, tossing halfway through cooking, until the tomatoes are burst and the asparagus are tender.

After the veggies are roasting for ~{10%minutes}, heat @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add the @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup} and remaining thyme and cook, stirring for ~{1%minute}. Add the warm stock, then reduce the heat to low, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}, until tender.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @scallions{2}, keeping the whites and greens separate. With ~{5%minutes} to go on the couscous, stir the scallion whites into the couscous.

Finish and serve: Fluff the couscous with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper. Divide the couscous between plates. Spoon the roasted veggies on top and garnish with the @almonds{1%oz}, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and scallion greens. Enjoy!